            Gate]|chapter=Prologue|passage=Thus, when he drew up instructions in lawyer language{{...}}his
            clerks{{...}}understood him very well. If he had written a love letter, or a farce, or a ''ballade'', or a
            story, no one, '''either''' clerks, or friends, or compositors, would have understood anything but a word
            here and a word there.}}
