==English==
            ===Alternative forms===
            * {{l|en|bycause}}, {{l|en|becos}}, {{l|en|'cause}}, {{l|en|cos}}, {{l|en|cuz}}, {{l|en|coz}},
            {{l|en|'cos}}, {{l|en|'cuz}}, {{l|en|'coz}}, {{l|en|b/c}}, {{l|en|bc}}, {{l|en|bcus}}
            ===Etymology===
            From {{inh|en|enm|bi cause}}, from {{m|enm|bi||by}} + {{m|enm|cause}}, modelled on {{der|en|fro|par cause}}.
            ===Pronunciation===
            * {{qualifier|stressed}}
            ** {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/bɪˈkɒz/}}
            ** {{a|UK, dated}} {{IPA|en|/bɪˈkɔːz/}}
            ** {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/biˈkɔz/|/biˈkʌz/|/bəˈkʌz/}}
            ** {{a|New England|obsolete}} {{IPA|en|/bɪˈkeɪz/}}
            * {{qualifier|unstressed}}
            ** {{IPA|en|/bɪkəz/}}
            * {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-because.wav|Audio (London)}}
            * {{audio|en|en-us-because.ogg|Audio (US)}}
            * {{hyphenation|en|be|cause}}
            * {{rhymes|en|ɒz|ʌz|s=2}}
            ===Adverb===
            {{en-adv|-}}
            # {{lb|en|archaic}} For the reason {{qualifier|that}}.
            #* {{RQ:KJV|Genesis|2|3||And God blessed the seventh day, and sanctified it: '''because''' that in it he had
            rested from all his work which God created and made.}}
            # On account {{qualifier|of}}, for sake {{qualifier|of}}.
            #: {{ux|en|My life is ruined '''because''' of you!}}
            # {{lb|en|by ellipsis}} {{non-gloss definition|Used alone to refuse to provide a full answer a question
            begun with "why", usually taken as an [[anapodoton]] of the elided full phrase "'''Because'''
            I said so".}}
