            ===Etymology===
            {{root|en|ine-pro|*preh₂-}}
            From {{inh|en|enm|for}}, from {{inh|en|ang|for||for, because of}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*furi||for}}, from
            {{der|en|ine-pro|*preh₂-}}.
            Cognate with {{cog|fy|foar||for}}, {{cog|nl|voor||for}}, {{cog|de|für||for}}, {{cog|da|for||for}},
            {{cog|sv|för||for}}, {{cog|no|for||for}}, {{cog|is|fyrir||for}}, {{cog|la|per||by, through, for, by means
            of}} and Romance language successors (e.g. {{cog|es|para||for}}), {{cog|grc|περί||for, about, toward}},
            {{cog|lt|per||by, through, during}}, {{cog|sa|परि||over, around|tr=pári}}.
            ===Pronunciation===
            * {{qualifier|stressed}} {{enPR|fôr}}
            ** {{a|UK}} {{IPA|en|/fɔː(ɹ)/}}
            ** {{a|US|CA}} {{IPA|en|/fɔɹ/}}
            ** {{a|AuE|NZ}} {{IPA|en|/foː(ɹ)/}}
            ** {{audio|en|en-us-for.ogg|Audio (US)}}
            ** {{audio|en|en-au-for.ogg|Audio (AU)}}
            ** {{rhymes|en|ɔː(ɹ)|s=1}}
            * {{qualifier|unstressed}} {{enPR|fər}}
            ** {{a|UK|AuE}} {{IPA|en|/fə(ɹ)/}}
            ** {{a|NZ}} {{IPA|en|/fɘ(ɹ)/}}
            ** {{a|US|CA}} {{IPA|en|/fɚ/|/fə/}}
            ** {{audio|en|en-us-for-unstressed.ogg|Audio (US), unstressed,<br> in the phrase "Wait for
            me".}}
            * {{homophones|en|fore|q1=with [[horse-hoarse merger]]|four|q2=with horse-hoarse merger}}
