            ====Preposition====
            {{ang-prep}}
            # [[because of]] ''(+ dative)''
            # {{l|en|for}} (for the [[sake]] of) ''(+ dative)''
            #* '''c. 990''', ''{{w|Wessex Gospels}}'',
            [https://archive.org/stream/dahalgangodspelo00thor#page/n145/mode/2up Luke 9:24]
            #*: {{quote|ang|''Sē þe his sāwle '''for''' mē forspilþ, hē hīe ġehǣlþ.''|Whoever destroys their soul
            '''for''' me will save it.}}
            # {{l|en|for}} (on behalf of, instead of) ''(+ accusative)''
            #* '''c. 992''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]],
            "[https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Homilies_of_the_Anglo-Saxon_Church/XXVII The Nativity of St. Paul
            the Apostle]"
            #*: {{quote|ang|''Petrus āna spræc '''for''' ealne þone hēap.''|Paul by himself spoke '''for''' the whole
            group.}}
            # [[ago]] ''(+ dative)''
            #* '''c. 995''', [[w:Ælfric of Eynsham|Ælfric]],
            [https://archive.org/stream/grammatik00aelfuoft#page/n12/mode/2up ''Extracts on Grammar in English'']
            #*: {{quote|ang|''Is nū for þȳ Godes þēowum and mynstermannum ġeorne tō wearnienne þæt sēo hālġe lār on ūrum
            dagum ne ācōliġe oþþe ātēoriġe swā swā hit wæs ġedōn on Angelcynne nū '''for''' ānum fēawum gēarum, swā þæt
            nān Englisċ prēost ne cūðe dihtan oþþe āsmēaġan ānne pistol on Lǣden, oþ þæt Dūnstān ærċebiscop and Æðelwold
            bisċop eft þā lāre on munuclīfum ārǣrdon.''|That's why God's servants and monks should be very careful not
            to let this sacred learning cool or fade in our time, the way it did in England a few years '''ago''', when
            none of our priests could compose or interpret a letter in Latin, until archbishop Dunstan and bishop
            Æthelwold revived learning in monastic life.}}
