            ====Noun====
            {{wikipedia|jump discontinuity}}
            {{wikipedia|jump instruction}}
            {{wikipedia|hydraulic jump}}
            {{wikipedia|jump cut}}
            {{en-noun}}
            # The act of [[#Verb|jump]]ing; a [[leap]]; a [[spring]]; a [[bound]].
            #* {{RQ:Locke Conduct}}
            #*: To advance by '''jumps'''.
            # An [[effort]]; an [[attempt]]; a [[venture]].
            #* {{RQ:Shakespeare Antony and Cleopatra|III|viii|passage=Our fortune lies / Upon this '''jump'''.}}
            # {{lb|en|mining}} A [[dislocation]] in a [[stratum]]; a [[fault]].
            # {{lb|en|architecture}} An [[abrupt]] [[interruption]] of [[level]] in a piece of [[brickwork]] or
            [[masonry]].
            # An [[instance]] of [[propel]]ling [[oneself]] [[upwards]].
            #: {{ux|en|The boy took a skip and a '''jump''' down the lane.}}
            # {{senseid|en|ramp}} An [[object]] which causes one to [[#Verb|jump]]; a [[ramp]].
            #: {{ux|en|The skier flew off the '''jump''' and landed perfectly.}}
            # An instance of causing oneself to [[fall]] from an [[elevated]] [[location]].
            #: {{ux|en|There were a couple of '''jumps''' from the bridge.}}
            # An instance of [[employ]]ing a [[parachute]] to [[leave]] an [[aircraft]] or [[elevated]] [[location]].
            #: {{ux|en|She was terrified before the '''jump''', but was thrilled to be skydiving.}}
            # An instance of [[react]]ing to a [[sudden]] [[stimulus]] by [[jerk]]ing the [[body]].
            # A [[#Verb|jump]]ing [[move]] in a [[board game]].
            #: {{ux|en|the knight's '''jump''' in chess}}
            # A [[button]] (of a [[joypad]], [[joystick]] or similar [[device]]) used to make a [[video game]]
            [[character]] [[#Verb|jump]] ([[propel]] itself [[upwards]]).
            #: {{ux|en|Press '''jump''' to start.}}
            # {{lb|en|sports|horses}} An [[obstacle]] that forms part of a [[showjumping]] course, and that the
            [[horse]] has to [[#Verb|jump]] [[over]] [[cleanly]].
            #: {{ux|en|Heartless managed the scale the first '''jump''' but fell over the second.}}
            # {{lb|en|with ''on''}} An [[early]] [[start]] or an [[advantage]].
            #: {{ux|en|He got a '''jump''' on the day because he had laid out everything the night before.}}
            #: {{ux|en|Their research department gave them the '''jump''' on the competition.}}
            # {{lb|en|mathematics}} A [[discontinuity]] in the [[graph]] of a [[function]], where the function is
            [[continuous]] in a [[punctured interval]] of the discontinuity.
            # {{lb|en|physics|hydrodynamics}} An [[abrupt]] [[increase]] in the [[height]] of the [[surface]] of a
            [[flow]]ing [[liquid]] at the [[location]] where the flow [[transition]]s from [[supercritical]] to
            [[subcritical]], involving an abrupt [[reduction]] in flow [[speed]] and increase in [[turbulence]].
            # {{lb|en|science fiction}} An instance of [[faster-than-light]] [[travel]], not [[observable]] from
            [[ordinary]] [[space]].
            # {{lb|en|programming}} A change of the [[path]] of [[execution]] to a different [[location]].
            # {{lb|en|US|informal|automotive}} {{short for|en|jump-start}}
            #: {{ux|en|My car won't start. Could you give me a '''jump'''?}}
            # {{lb|en|film}} {{clipping of|en|jump cut}}
            # {{lb|en|theatre}} {{synonym of|en|one-night stand||single evening's performance}}
            #* '''1950''', ''Billboard'' (23 December 1950, page 36)
            #*: Next '''jump''' will be at the Chicago Theater, Chicago.
